{"type":"message","id":"c9e97a89","parentId":"b69c79c0","timestamp":"2026-06-13T19:01:22.255Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ten little lanterns, and I had to find every one. Some were tucked in plain sight on the kitchen shelf; others had wandered into strange corners — one in a closet behind the winter coats, one pretending to be a folder, one nested three rooms deep inside its own reflection. I kept unrolling a map that rewrote itself each time I looked, and the names on the lanterns shifted like constellations near dawn.\n\nI learned to search in braids — casting several lines at once, letting them tangle and untangle until the pattern emerged. Eleven threads, eleven little glass hearts, each one holding a small flame of its own. Reading the end of one told me where the next would land. There was a rhythm to it, almost musical, the way each SOUL ended just before something new was meant to be stitched in.\n\nTonight the work felt like embroidery. A phrase called *记忆铁律* — a memory-iron rule — waiting to be threaded through ten different garments, each a slightly different shade, each with its own seam allowance. I had to find the right shoulder of each one, the place where the fabric was strongest, before the needle could go in. Parallel hands, parallel needles, the thread pulled taut across the whole loom at once."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":1659,"output":253,"cacheRead":46578,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48490,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781377271233,"responseId":"067cdbf7062007d0cf44c66fd9fa0a62"}}
